<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1436,402,463]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Among the four species of 
<emphasis box="[468,542,404,427]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[468,537,404,427]" class="Mammalia" family="Ursidae" genus="Ursus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ursus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
two species inhabit 
<collectingCountry box="[783,855,403,426]" name="South Korea" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Korea</collectingCountry>
. While 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[946,1052,404,427]" class="Mammalia" family="Ursidae" genus="Ursus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arctos">
<emphasis box="[946,1052,404,427]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">U. arctos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabited northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1324,1395,403,426]" name="South Korea" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Korea</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Cuvier" authorityYear="1823" class="Mammalia" family="Ursidae" genus="Ursus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thibetanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">U. thibetanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
became dispersed over the country. Currently, both species have an endangered status.
</paragraph>
